```

> Also, I'm wonding if Solidity team removed nulls, then now can we detect that certain things are present / absent via AST?


Removing null properties in JSON is recommended in [Google JSON style guide](https://google.github.io/styleguide/jsoncstyleguide.xml?showone=Empty/Null_Property_Values#Empty/Null_Property_Values)

Here is an example mentioned there:

```
{
  "volume": 10,

  // Even though the "balance" property's value is zero, it should be left in,
  // since "0" signifies "even balance" (the value could be "-1" for left
  // balance and "+1" for right balance.
  "balance": 0,

  // The "currentlyPlaying" property can be left out since it is null.
  // "currentlyPlaying": null
}
```

We only remove members such as `documentation: null`. The use cases you mentioned above will be unaffected.


